cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper focuses on learning joint language-visual embeddings for natural language video annotation and search, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates neural network models on a large-scale dataset, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a multiple-choice test for evaluating visual-language models, which could be considered as multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
